document_data.name: Temnodontosaurus
document_data.mainbody: '''Temnodontosaurus''', also known as '''tennodontosaurus''' ({{Pronounce|ten|a|dan|to|SAR|us|refs={{Cite dragon/93/Ay pronunseeAYshun gyd|30}}}}), was a species of ichthyosaur living in [[Faer√ªn]].
document_data.Combat: Temnodontosaurs were one of the top predators in their territory. Despite its size, they were very fast. They were ferocious predators, especially when they were in the midst of a feeding frenzy. They used their long, powerful tail as a weapon against prey and competing predators.
document_data.Habitat: Temnodontosaurs lived in the ocean, often sharing territory with [[mosasaurs]].
document_data.Biology: Temnodontosaurs were carnivores and solitary creatures. Their young was birthed live within the ocean. Temnodontosaurs were air breathers and as a result needed to frequently surface to breathe.
